Ad Text:
Lynch Group is recruiting a hands-on SAP Integration Technical Lead to own the design, delivery and operational stability of integrations for our SAP S/4HANA Public Cloud landscape. This is a senior technical lead role (no direct reports). You will provide technical leadership for integration architecture, HANA modelling for reporting (side-by-side/analytics environments), and manage third-party vendors who deliver development and integration work.

Role scope — technical lead: This is a hands-on technical role responsible for integration architecture, data provisioning and analytics support. Detailed functional requirements elicitation, or running stakeholder workshops. The Integration Lead converts business/BA requirements into technical designs and implements them; the business/BA teams retain ownership of functional requirements and acceptance.

Key responsibilities

· Lead design and delivery of interfaces using SAP Integration Suite (Cloud Integration / CPI), API Management and SAP BTP.

· Design, build and support iFlows in CPI — adapter configuration, message mapping (graphical/XSLT), Groovy for custom logic, error subprocesses, retries and production monitoring.

· Design and optimise SAP HANA data models (Calculation, Analytical and Attribute Views) for reporting and integration in side-by-side HANA/HANA Cloud environments.

· Implement data provisioning strategies suitable for S/4 Public Cloud (API/OData extraction, SDI / HANA Cloud replication or other side-by-side approaches).

· Manage third-party vendors and contractors: define SoWs, perform technical acceptance testing, enforce SLAs, and remediate performance or security issues.

· Provide senior production support, incident triage and root-cause analysis; participate in a rostered on-call rotation.

· Define and maintain integration standards, governance and operational runbooks; mentor internal engineers.

Essential

· 5+ years SAP technical experience with 3+ years hands-on SAP Integration Suite / CPI experience (iFlows, adapters, mappings).

· Strong experience in SAP HANA data modelling and performance optimisation (calculation/analytical/attribute views) in side-by-side/analytics environments.

· Proven experience implementing API/OData-based integrations and performing technical acceptance.

· Demonstrated experience managing third-party vendors/outsourced development.

· Knowledge of secure authentication (OAuth, SAML, certificates) and protocols (OData, REST, SOAP, RFC, IDoc, SFTP).

· Excellent stakeholder and communication skills.

Highly regarded

· API Management, Event Mesh, SAP BTP services, HANA Cloud/SDI experience.

· Groovy/Java/XSLT or graphical mapping experience.

· Relevant SAP certifications.

Other

· Based at Ingleburn. Occasional travel and China engagement possible.

· Pre-employment police/background check required.

About IMDEX 

At IMDEX, we create technology that efficiently and sustainably unlocks the Earth’s value. Our technologies and products allow smarter and safer decisions for people, assets and the earth. Through innovation and curiosity, we continue to find new ways to improve accuracy and efficiency in mining in a more sustainable way. For further information visit www.imdex.com.

 


The opportunity 

IMDEX is on a bold journey to expand its digital footprint, recently acquiring three cutting-edge technology companies. To support this exciting growth, we’re creating a brand-new role — Finance Integration Analyst for an 15-18 month fixed term contract.

As a Finance Integration Analyst, you will support the Finance Integration Manager in executing integration activities for mergers and acquisitions. Your focus will be on financial analysis, process alignment, and system integration to ensure accurate reporting and compliance during transitions. Success in this role means delivering timely, high-quality integration outcomes and supporting global finance teams.

Main responsibilities include:

·       Assist with finance integration activities for acquired entities.

·       Deliver accounting requirements including month-end, half-year, and annual processes.

·       Align acquired entities with IMDEX group accounting policies and systems.

·       Support budgeting and forecasting processes for integrated entities.

·       Act as a finance business partner to acquired companies and internal stakeholders.

·       Identify and implement process improvements and standardisation.




What you will bring

You’re a proactive finance professional with a sharp eye for detail and a passion for integration. You thrive in dynamic environments and enjoy working across teams to drive meaningful change. With a strong foundation in accounting and a collaborative mindset, you’re ready to take on integration projects that span continents. To thrive in this role, you will need:

Essential:

Degree in Accounting/Finance or similar, CA/CPA qualified.

Minimum 6 years’ experience in a global/multi-national company or Big-4 environment.

Strong knowledge of financial accounting processes and month-end close.

Advanced MS Excel skills and analytical mindset.

Excellent communication, planning, and coordination skills.

Ability to thrive in a dynamic, changing environment.

Willingness to travel internationally as required.

Desirable

Experience in M&A projects, financial integration or finance transformation.



At IMDEX - we do things differently

IMDEX is a unique blend of technology and mining. Our people have contrasting and complementary skills which drive innovation, adaptability, and holistic problem solving.

We offer our global talent:

A culture of care – we care and look out for our people by fostering an inclusive and respectful working environment.

Opportunities to grow – we want you to grow and expand your thinking and provide clear career pathways so you can see where you can go next.

Empowerment by purpose – to be close to the solution and change the face of mining forever.

Ability to build strong connections within a global business – you will have the opportunity to collaborate with people from all over the world.

The role of Data Engineer will be a key contributor to the migration of our client's reporting platform, focusing on back-end systems and data infrastructure. This role is responsible for ensuring the smooth integration and processing of large-scale data, building robust data pipelines, and creating scalable data products to support multiple applications across the company. The Data Engineer will collaborate with various departments to implement and maintain high-performance data systems that empower business users with actionable insights. Responsibilities also include optimizing data workflows, driving innovation in data engineering processes, and ensuring data integrity throughout the platform migration.




Main responsibilities:

· Collaboration: Partner with cross-functional teams to understand their data needs and design solutions that streamline data flows and integration across multiple applications.

· Semantic Model & KPI Definitions: Build and maintain a comprehensive semantic model, working closely with stakeholders to define and standardize KPIs that align with business objectives and reporting requirements.

· Platform Migration: help with back-end migration efforts, ensuring that all data pipelines, storage solutions, and processing systems are transitioned efficiently and without disruption to business operations.

· Data Pipeline Development: Design, build, and maintain scalable and efficient data pipelines that ensure accurate and timely data delivery to support business intelligence tools and applications.

· System Optimization: Continuously optimize and monitor back-end systems, databases, and data workflows to maintain high performance and cost-efficiency.

· Data Integration: Ensure seamless integration of data from various sources into centralized platforms, enabling comprehensive reporting and analysis capabilities.

· Problem-Solving: Leverage data engineering expertise to troubleshoot issues, optimize performance, and solve complex challenges related to data storage, processing, and accessibility.

· Innovation & Collaboration: Work closely with the Data & IT teams to explore new technologies and methodologies, driving innovation in the company's data engineering practices and supporting evolving business needs.




Requirements:

Must have

University Degree (Data Engineering, Information Systems, or a related field)

3+ years in a data engineering or similar role, with demonstrated success in supporting data transformation and migration projects, ideally from legacy systems to modern data platforms

Proven track record in supporting data transformation projects, nice to have would be migrating from legacy systems to modern BI tools like Power BI

Technical Skills:

Data Transformation: Strong experience in ETL/ELT processes, data modeling, and reporting in Microsoft environment (SSIS, Azure DataFactory, Synapse, Fabric)

Power BI Semantic Model: Proven ability to create and maintain a comprehensive analytical data models, specifically in Power BI and/or Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services (SSAS), including KPI definitions and metric standardization to meet reporting requirements

SQL Proficiency: Proficient in SQL (any dialect) for data manipulation, transformation, and analysis.

DAX Proficiency: Proficient in DAX language for Analysis Services/Power BI.

Data Pipelines: Experience building and optimizing data pipelines for large-scale data processing.

Cloud Experience: Familiarity with cloud environments such as Azure, with a focus on tools like Synapse Analytics

Ability to analyze both structured and unstructured data, with a proactive approach to identifying and solving data issues

Effective communication skills to collaborate with stakeholders across departments, strong problem-solving abilities, and a commitment to data quality and accuracy

English at business level

Visa sponsorship is available for candidates without existing Australian work rights

Nice to have

· Experience with SSRS and SSIS, or similar reporting and integration tools

· Hands-on experience with BI tools like Power BI, with a strong understanding of KPI definitions and dashboard creation

A bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Management, or a related field.

About the Company 

Ahrens is a fifth-generation, Australian family-owned company, with over 120 years’ experience in delivering a wide range of high-quality and cost-effective products and projects across Australia, with footprints overseas.  

Our growth has culminated in the business we are today: a full Construction, Engineering, Mining & Industrial Services, Sheds & Silos and Water Storage company which provides complete turnkey project solutions, supported by our 26 divisions.  

As we continue to evolve, so does our need to heavily invest in our people and facilities for continued success.

About the Role 

Our IT team is growing, and we’re recruiting multiple Business Analysts including this Senior IT Business Analyst role. The Senior IT Business Analyst drives enterprise-wide change across people, processes, and technology, with a strong focus on technology enabled initiatives and application optimisation.

The role combines senior level business analysis with hands on responsibility for the configuration, support, and continuous improvement of core business systems. Working across agile, waterfall, and hybrid delivery models, the role partners with business and technical teams to translate requirements into secure, practical solutions, while ensuring system reliability and supporting continuous improvement and successful transformation outcomes.

This role will be working across the Ahrens Group and specifically working on projects at our Vaughan Constructions division. 

Skills and Experience 

The successful candidate must have tertiary qualifications in ICT related disciplines and proven experience in a similar role, ideally from a fast paced and busy IT support environment.

Ahrens is seeking a dynamic team player with strong written and verbal communication skills, who can build and maintain relationships with a range of stakeholders at different levels across the business.

This role requires excellent problem-solving skills, as well as strong experience with systems implementation and support. Candidates who are familiar and experienced with a broad portfolio of business applications are highly desirable for this role. 

Benefits 

Employee Assistance Program, supporting you and your family’s health & wellbeing 

Discounts to some of Australia’s leading corporate partners in private health insurance, gyms, travel, clothing, vehicles and more

Family, social and team building events including Friday afternoon team bonding 

Opportunities for career progression

About the Organisation

Life Without Barriers is a leading social purpose, not for profit organisation of 8,000 employees working in more than 500 communities across Australia. We support children, young people and families, people with disability, older people and people with mental illness. We work with people who are homeless and refugees and asylum seekers.

Make a real difference in the lives of vulnerable Australians with this unique opportunity to provide both corporate expertise and community support. With a focus on people, not profit, Life Without Barriers’ corporate services team partners with our direct support staff, clients, and their families to ensure we continue our mission to change lives for the better. If a truly inclusive, collaborative, and fast-paced work environment sounds like your next career move, this is an opening not to be missed.

We want to employ people who reflect the diversity of our clients to ensure we can support each client’s individual needs and wants. We encourage people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander background and people with disability to apply.

About the role

Permanent full time position that can be located anywhere in Australia where you have full flexibility to work from home or one of our offices. 

This role places you at the centre of how data, analytics, and insight enable the organisation to operate at scale and make better decisions. As the Data Platforms & Analytics Manager, you will be accountable for the reliability, evolution, and effective use of the organisation’s enterprise data platforms and analytics capabilities.

You will combine strong technical and analytical judgement with practical leadership, ensuring data platforms are trusted, secure, scalable, and fit for purpose. You will lead a multidisciplinary team of data engineers, analysts, data governance and platform specialists, enabling the delivery of high-quality analytics and data products that support reporting, automation, AI, and digital initiatives across the organisation.

Reporting to the Head of Digital, Data & AI, you will translate business priorities and analytics use cases into clear delivery plans and platform roadmaps. You will balance delivery momentum with long-term platform stewardship, managing risk, technical debt, and vendor dependencies while ensuring data is reliable and usable for frontline and corporate decision-making. 

Key Responsibilities

Own the day-to-day operation and evolution of enterprise data platforms and analytics capabilities
Translate business and analytics needs into prioritised delivery plans and platform roadmaps
Lead and develop a high-performing data and analytics team through clear direction, coaching, and support
Ensure data platforms and analytics products are reliable, secure, and production-ready
Manage data quality, platform risks, technical debt, and operational incidents
Embed practical data governance, privacy, and security controls into platforms and analytics solutions
Partner with stakeholders to communicate progress, risks, and outcomes clearly
Drive continuous improvement in data platform practices, analytics delivery, and value realisation

Skills & Experience

Proven experience delivering and operating enterprise data platforms and analytics solutions
Strong understanding of data architectures, integration patterns, and analytics enablement
Experience leading multidisciplinary data or analytics teams in complex environments
Demonstrated accountability for delivery outcomes, platform reliability, and data quality
Working knowledge of data governance, privacy, and security requirements
Strong problem-solving, prioritisation, and decision-making capability
Ability to communicate effectively with technical and non-technical stakeholders

Successful candidates will be required to clear probity checks including a National Criminal History Record Check.

Benefits

Opportunity to shape and lead enterprise data and analytics capabilities with real organisational impact
Meaningful work supporting vulnerable communities across Australia
Option to fully Work from Home (WFH)
Competitive salary packaging and not-for-profit benefits + monthly rostered days off

Our ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with a passion for data and commercial outcomes. You combine your analytical experience in the retail, FMCG or consultancy industries with strong analytical skills with the ability to tell a compelling story through data, powered by your proficiency in Excel, data visualisation tools, financial modelling and business case development. Most importantly, you’re collaborative, detail-oriented, and able to communicate complex insights in a clear, actionable way. This role would be best suited to a Category Management SME who loves to delve into the data and drive outcomes through data-led storytelling.

You’ll also ideally have:

Tertiary qualification in Business, Analytics, Economics, or related field
Proven experience in business analysis, insights, or commercial analytics within FMCG/retail or consultancy
Strong analytical and data interpretation skills with high attention to detail
Proficiency in Excel and data visualisation tools (Power BI, Tableau)
Experience in financial modelling and business case development
Ability to communicate insights clearly to non-technical stakeholders

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Job Title: Senior Analyst - Debt Advisory - Capital Markets Group
Category: Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services)
Ad Text:
Join JLL's elite Capital Markets team and accelerate your career in Debt Advisory.




As a Senior Analyst in our Debt Advisory division, you'll work directly with our Executive Directors and Co-Heads of Debt & Structured Finance to execute complex finance transactions that define Australia and New Zealand's real estate finance landscape.




Key Responsibilities:

Execute debt placements and capital raising assignments for marquee clients

Build sophisticated financial models that drive investment and development finance decisions

Create compelling pitch materials and deliver presentations to financiers and clients 

Manage due diligence processes and coordinate with key stakeholders

Develop strategic client relationships and provide ongoing transaction support

Conduct market research and analysis that shapes industry strategies

Project manage the continuous improvement of team processes and best practices




Why Choose This Role: 




Professional Growth - Gain exposure to diverse asset classes and cutting-edge finance strategies while working on landmark transactions.


Expert Mentorship - Learn directly from industry leaders in our collaborative, high-performance environment.




Technology Advantage: Access AI-powered market intelligence and digital platforms that amplify deal exposure globally, providing tools that most competitors simply don't have.




Competitive Rewards – Competitive compensation package and career development opportunities.




What You Bring: 

Bachelor's degree in Finance, Economics, Real Estate, or related discipline

Proven experience in real estate finance, banking, or related field

Excel proficiency with strong financial modeling and valuation capabilities

Exceptional analytical thinking and problem-solving abilities

Outstanding written and verbal communication skills

Attention to detail and ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously

Ability to excel in a fast-paced, deadline-driven and collaborative environment




What JLL Can Offer You:

Premium office space and workplace perks. Enjoy all the complimentary barista beverages of your choice in a collaborative environment that supports your professional growth

Recognition benefits

Corporate discounts and offers

'You' Days

Health & Wellbeing programs

Learning & Development platforms

Mentorship from industry-leading professionals

Paid time off for volunteer work




As an organisation, we don’t just accept that we are a place of many different people, but we embrace it, we celebrate it, and we proactively support the needs that difference brings. JLL is committed to equal opportunity and building an inclusive workplace. This is why, for more than a decade, we continue to rank among the World’s Most Ethical Companies. We support applications from all underrepresented groups, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders, LGBT+, people with disability and people of all age, religions and race. We are dedicated to offering veterans from all ranks and services a successful civilian career as they transition out of the military. We recognise and appreciate the skills acquired in their service careers as vital and transferable to our workforce.




Apply today, quoting job reference number REQ471757.

Job Title: 2 x Principal Advisor, Strategic Insights, Premier and Cabinet
Category:
Strategy & Planning (Consulting & Strategy)
Government - State (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Are you curious, open-minded, responsive and agile? Do you have experience working collaboratively with senior stakeholders across government, academia and industry? This role could be for you. We are seeking a Principal Advisor, Strategic Insights, to play a key role in our Implementation Division in the Department of the Premier and Cabinet. Working at the heart of Queensland Government decision making, you will use your research, insights and foresight expertise; strong networks, communication skills and eye for detail to enhance delivery of current and future priorities. You will provide strategic insights and foresight to support proactive responses to emerging societal and economic shifts. If you have experience in horizon scanning, trends storytelling and research and strong presentation skills, this job is ideal for you.

About us:
For more than 165 years, the Department of the Premier and Cabinet has been building the foundations of Queensland. As the central policy agency for the Queensland Government, our people influence and impact the work at the core of our state's public sector.

The Strategic Insights unit equips the Queensland Government with forward-looking insights, uncovering emerging opportunities and risks, empowering decision-makers to create a brighter future. Our mission is to discover the new the opportunities of tomorrow, while exploring and identifying new insights to address the challenges of today.

How you'll contribute:
As a senior team member, you will lead research, develop strategic insights, implement foresights and futures methodologies, and deliver high quality briefs. In this role, you will:
• Mentor team members in strategic thinking, frameworks and processes.
• Use your extensive professional networks while continuing to build strong stakeholder relationships.
• Lead trends scanning, secondary research, and expert consultations to inform evidence-based reporting.
• Facilitate workshops, engage with the community, and influence executives through high-level discussions and engaging presentations.
• Manage projects to deliver high-quality outputs with speed and efficiency.
• Communicate complex ideas with clarity and influence.

What you'll bring to the role:
Due to the critical nature of this role and its proximity to central government decision making, you will have the following attributes:
• History of high performance and productivity.
• Attention to detail and commitment to quality.
• Agility to adapt rapidly to changing priorities.
• Experience working in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
• High-level, professional communication skills.
• Positive and open-minded with commitment to a growth mindset.
• Visionary and future focused.

Candidates with a background working in a central agency, consulting, commercial strategy or in fast-paced, high-performing teams will be highly regarded.

Why Join Us?
At DPC, you'll be part of a team that leads and connects the public sector, delivering outstanding advice and services that impact Queensland's future. It's in your hands.

How to apply:
Please provide a one-page cover letter outlining your interest and suitability for the role and a tailored resume highlighting your relevant work experience. Further information on the responsibilities of the role is in the role description. You are strongly encouraged to review the applicant guide prior to applying. DPC is committed to working with you to discuss adjustments to ensure you can best
demonstrate your suitability for the role. If you would like to discuss the role or would like additional support/adjustments during recruitment, please contact Kathy Benson on Ph: 0438 663 857.

Applications to remain current for 12 months.

Job Ad Reference: QLD/676607/26

Closing Date: Friday, 06 February 2026

Job Description


Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work, we trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

What you’d be doing in this role

As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.

At the moment, this role is focused on:
 

Team Lead - Lead, mentor, and grow the Design Research team—building research capability, fostering psychological safety, and developing consistent standards of excellence across evaluative and generative methods.

Future research - Craft and lead a design research strategy that informs product vision, company goals, and long-term opportunities in an AI era.

Close the Loop (evaluative) research - Drive streams of work to find and fix user issues across Canva’s product surfaces by identifying and close loops, and to ensure an objectively high quality bar

Self-serve research - Enable product teams to confidently conduct their own research through training, templates, and shared frameworks - while maintaining a strong quality bar

Sub-specialty lead - Evolve the Design Research sub specialty by strengthening methodologies, elevating craft standards, and integrating AI-assisted techniques that improve speed, quality, and scale.

Set and maintain a quality bar for design research - both via hands-on research, and coaching, training, processes, and oversight

Autonomy & Decision Making: Sets direction for the group with clarity and confidence, defining priorities and navigating trade-offs across multiple teams, while aligning to strategic direction

Lead communications to all relevant company goal stakeholders

Drive prioritisation so that this key resource is focused on the key priorities

Insight Impact, Measurement and Communication - define and measure research success metrics

Define and manage the research tool ecosystem - including AI-enabled platforms that improve insight generation, collaboration, and organisational understanding.

You're probably a match if:

You're a Seasoned leader with deep expertise across generative, evaluative, and mixed-methods research

Motivated by shaping product strategy, elevating research craft, and integrating emerging AI capabilities into meaningful practice

AI resesarch native, consistently learning and evolving skills as fast as the technology is unlocking capabilities

Skilled leader to ensure the team has the right strategy, quality bar, and delivery

Passionate about using research to drive business and product strategy to delight our community, from the most high level strategy all the way to specific product details

Strong stakeholder management and communications skills to partner with senior leaders and ICs across Product, Design, Engineering, and Data

Force multiplier to amplify the impact of research by unlocking Product teams across Canva to conduct their own research

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too

Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers

An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more

Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Job Title: Health Data Informatics AI Team Lead
Ad Text:
For over 40 years, our shared commitment to curing childhood cancer has united us. Together, we continue to accelerate the answers to make that possible.

To accomplish our vision, we’re seeking someone who lives our values: owning and delivering meaningful work, collaborating to drive impact, challenging the status quo to create a better future, and balancing logic with empathy. Let’s achieve more, together.

The Health Data Informatics & AI Team Lead will accelerate existing efforts within Children’s Cancer Institute Computational Biology Group to shape the next generation of AI-enabled health data solutions at Children’s Cancer Institute. This newly created role will guide the development of advanced AI systems for health data collection and harmonisation, rapid molecular reporting, tumour classification, and knowledge graph creation. These initiatives already underpin national-scale precision medicine programs and are critical for improving diagnostic accuracy, supporting translational research and enabling real-world data reuse. 

Beyond technical delivery, this role will provide strategic leadership: defining and executing our AI roadmap, expanding institutional capability in health data informatics, and driving the adoption of innovative approaches like LLMs, RAG, and generative AI. The Health Data Informatics & AI Team Lead will also build key partnerships with technology and research leaders to deliver scalable, ethical, and interoperable solutions, ensuring CCI remains at the forefront of digital health innovation.

To succeed you will have…

A PhD in Computer Science, AI, Bioinformatics, Computational Biology, Biomedical Engineering, or a closely related discipline, with demonstrated experience in regulated healthcare environments. 
CHIA (Certified Health Informatician Australasia) certification would be highly desirable
Proven track record of leading scientific or technical teams in a research-intensive environment. 
Demonstrated experience in applying AI/ML techniques to clinical or biomedical data, including multi-omic analysis. 
Experience in working with health data, clinical workflows, and medical research contexts. 
Experience in designing and conducting research experiments and contributing to intellectual property or scientific invention. 
Excellent communication and collaboration skills, including the ability to work effectively with clinical, technical, legal, and governance stakeholders. 
Experience building partnerships with technology or industry partners (desirable)

We will support you to be your best with benefits that include but are not limited to:

Working in a world-class, purpose-built facility, the only one in Australia dedicated to curing childhood cancer
Focus on employee wellbeing, including up to 5 gifted wellbeing days off (paid) per year
Access to Fitness Passport, with access to an extensive choice of fitness facilities across Sydney at discounted rates
Corporate discounts and discounts on education through UNSW

Join us to shape a future every child deserves and to find meaning in your own. Because together, we can cure every child of cancer. It’s not if, it’s when.

Additional information about Children's Cancer Institute can be found on our website at: https://www.ccia.org.au/jobs-study . We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Children’s Cancer Institute and our culture.  We embrace diversity and encourage you to advise of any reasonable adjustments you may need during the recruitment process.
